AuthFormHandler: earlyReturn() should exit on BATCH_MODE_ABORTED

The only modes where it is valid to automatically submit forms are
BATCH_MODE_ENABLED and BATCH_MODE_EMPTY_ONLY.  For BATCH_MODE_ABORTED
we need to act as though the user clicked the 'disconnect' button.

Reported-by: Ingo Zansinger <ingo@zansinger.de>
Signed-off-by: Kevin Cernekee <cernekee@gmail.com>

AuthFormHandler: Fix empty group_list submission

If the saved authgroup is the default authgroup (the first or the only one
in the list), the group_list field may be left NULL and the gateway might
reject logon attempts.

Reported-by: Ingo Zansinger <ingo@zansinger.de>

AuthFormHandler: Fix another setAuthgroup() corner case

Make sure that autogroupOpt.value always gets populated if we have
a saved authgroup.  If we don't have a saved authgroup but the gateway
offers an authgroup dropdown, don't try to log on using batch mode.
